=== Formula Provider ===

==== Functionality ====

Creates new information based on the results of a SPARQL query.

{{#widget: com.fluidops.iwb.widget.DisplayConfigurationWidget
| clazz = com.fluidops.iwb.provider.FormulaProvider
| type = 'DESCRIPTION'
}}
Go back to [[Help:Providers | Providers ]]

==== Configuration Settings ====
{{#widget: com.fluidops.iwb.widget.DisplayConfigurationWidget
| clazz = com.fluidops.iwb.provider.FormulaProvider
}}

==== Example ====

Let's assume that there is a naming convention where the first three letters of an asset
denote the customer the asset belongs to. The formula provider with this query materializes
this naming convention into an explicit statement:

<source>
select 
    ?asset 
    (:customer as ?pred ) 
    ?cust 
where 
{ 
    ?asset rdfs:label ?label 
    BIND (URI(concat('http://www.fluidops.com/', SUBSTR(?label,1,3))) AS ?cust) 
}
</source>
